$$A = (2.99792458	imes 10^{10}\,	ext{s}^{-1}) 	imes 1760 \approx 5.276347 	imes 10^{13}\,	ext{s}^{-1}$$
The barrier height is $E_{0}=80.0\,	ext{kJ mol}^{-1}$. The rate constants are evaluated at two energies, $E_{1}=120\,	ext{kJ mol}^{-1}$ and $E_{2}=200\,	ext{kJ mol}^{-1}$. Since the energy term is a ratio, the units cancel and we can use $	ext{kJ mol}^{-1}$ directly.

For $E_{1} = 120\,	ext{kJ mol}^{-1}$:
$$k(E_{1}) = A \left(1 -  rac{E_{0}}{E_{1}}ight)^{2} = (5.276347 	imes 10^{13}\,	ext{s}^{-1}) \left(1 -  rac{80.0}{120}ight)^{2}$$
$$k(E_{1}) = (5.276347 	imes 10^{13}\,	ext{s}^{-1}) \left(1 -  rac{2}{3}ight)^{2} = (5.276347 	imes 10^{13}\,	ext{s}^{-1}) \left( rac{1}{3}ight)^{2}$$
$$k(E_{1}) =  rac{5.276347 	imes 10^{13}}{9}\,	ext{s}^{-1} \approx 5.862608 	imes 10^{12}\,	ext{s}^{-1}$$
Rounding to four significant figures, $k(E_{1}) = 5.863 	imes 10^{12}\,	ext{s}^{-1}$.

For $E_{2} = 200\,	ext{kJ mol}^{-1}$:
$$k(E_{2}) = A \left(1 -  rac{E_{0}}{E_{2}}ight)^{2} = (5.276347 	imes 10^{13}\,	ext{s}^{-1}) \left(1 -  rac{80.0}{200}ight)^{2}$$
$$k(E_{2}) = (5.276347 	imes 10^{13}\,	ext{s}^{-1}) \left(1 - 0.4ight)^{2} = (5.276347 	imes 10^{13}\,	ext{s}^{-1}) (0.6)^{2}$$
$$k(E_{2}) = (5.276347 	imes 10^{13}\,	ext{s}^{-1}) 	imes 0.36 \approx 1.899485 	imes 10^{13}\,	ext{s}^{-1}$$
Rounding to four significant figures, $k(E_{2}) = 1.899 	imes 10^{13}\,	ext{s}^{-1}$.
